properties.areaDesc: Coastal Waters from Schoodic Point, ME to Stonington, ME out 25 NM; Coastal Waters from Eastport, ME to Schoodic Point, ME out 25 NM
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued February 7 at 10:59PM EST until February 8 at 5:00AM EST by NWS Caribou ME
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 25 to 35 kt with gusts up to 40 kt and seas 15
to 20 feet expected, subsiding to 10 to 15 feet.

* WHERE...Coastal Waters from Eastport, ME to Schoodic Point, ME
out 25 NM and Coastal Waters from Schoodic Point, ME to
Stonington, ME out 25 NM.

* WHEN...Until 5 AM EST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Very strong winds will cause hazardous seas which
could capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 AM EST SATURDAY... ...STORM WARNING IS CANCELLED
